### ============================================================
###  AUTH MODULE  — /api/v1/auth
### ============================================================

### [1] Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Rahul Sharma",
    "email": "rahul@gmail.com",
    "password": "password123",
    "username": "rahul_07"
}

###

### [2] Register — Validation Error (short password)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Test User",
    "email": "test@gmail.com",
    "password": "123",
    "username": "testuser"
}

###

### [3] Register — Conflict Error (duplicate email/username)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Rahul Again",
    "email": "rahul8@gmail.com",
    "password": "password123",
    "username": "rahul_08"
}

###

### [4] Login — Success
# After running: copy the token from the response and paste into @token above
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "rahul8@gmail.com",
    "password": "password123"
}

###

### [5] Login — Wrong Password (Unauthorized)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "rahul8@gmail.com",
    "password": "wrongpassword"
}

###

### [6] Login — Non-existent User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "nobody@gmail.com",
    "password": "password123"
}

###

### [7] Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###


### ============================================================
###  USER MODULE  — /api/v1/users
### ============================================================

### [8] Get User by ID — Success
# Set @userId to the _id from your register/login response
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}} HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [9] Get User by ID — Not Found
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/000000000000000000000001 HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [10] Get User by ID — No Token (Unauthorized)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}} HTTP/1.1

###

### [11] Search Users — by name or username
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search?q=rahul&page=1&limit=10 HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [12] Search Users — empty query (Validation Error)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search?q= HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [13] Update Profile — username only
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}} HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "username": "rahul_updated"
}

###

### [14] Update Profile — profilePicture only
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}} HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "profilePicture": "https://example.com/avatar/rahul.jpg"
}

###

### [15] Update Profile — Empty body (Validation Error)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}} HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{}

###

### [16] Update Profile — Attempting to update another user (Forbidden)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/000000000000000000000001 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "username": "hacker_attempt"
}

###

### [17] Soft Delete (Deactivate Account)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}} HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [18] Soft Delete — Own account check after deactivation
# Expect: User not found (active = false)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}} HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
